Hello! I handled this today.
first complaint: we need flight logs that are pretty. Black is boring, pink isn't even pink, but salmon.
I've wanted to fly since I was very young.
And I did it today... today, I piloted an airplane. I still can't believe it.
FlightAware data.
I'll try to do it still this Saturday. The weather isn't great right now, but it's only Monday.
Difficulties are already starting to show up. I'm probably going to have BEAUCOUP of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will take ÉNORMÉMENT of time and require BEAUCOUP of extra work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve and, for now, it seems *totally* manageable. It's just that it will take a lot of time and money.
In case the challenge ahead interests you.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They do not issue a medical certificate if one is on treatment for it.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I ever get a personalized license plate number, it WILL BE a variation of N1337_, with _ corresponding to any available final alphabetical character.
Naturally, the sun will be shining while I am away, lol. What a failure.
I need to go flying again. And the weather isn't helping.
Welcome to the world of general aviation 😜
I have the impression that aviation tends to follow a rather conservative line based on the ads that YouTube has decided I should see, the videos that are recommended to me, and the comments I can see.
If the weather is good, I'll fly again on Saturday.
