Good Saturday morning. I did this today ^_^
#TeaganAir
C'est officiellement inscrit dans mon carnet de vol. J'ai 2,3 heures ^_^
#TeaganAir
Si vous voulez savoir quel effet ça fait de piloter un petit avion, je dirais que c'est comme conduire une moto/un quad et un bateau à 4 000 pieds d'altitude
Sur la terme ferme, tout s'accélère très vite. Il y a un certain degré d'instabilité au sol, d'où la sensation de moto/quad.
And also, just in case you didn't know, on the ground, you steer an airplane with your feet, not with the yoke. Steering pedals and brakes. It's not a car.
In the air, it shakes and wobbles, it feels like being in a boat on water. You have control, but sometimes a wave comes to knock you off balance, so you need to be sea-legs, but in the air.
Oh, one more little thing :
Flying is physical. Today, I have sore muscles in my back and legs as if I had gone to the gym.
It's not like taking a car for a Sunday drive. It's much closer to a sport than a walk in my novice perspective.
Bon samedi mes trésors. Bienvenue à 4 000 pieds.
I'll be back tomorrow, and we'll do some descents and slow flight.
Today was quite eventful, but great. We did some slow flight and descents. At one point, ground speed dropped to 16 miles per hour, for an airspeed of 65.
It was a clear day with a bit of fog at higher altitudes, but it was still pleasant nonetheless.
Follow-up with FlightAware data.
